  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We review the physical motivations and the mathematical results obtained so far in the isocone-based approach to noncommutative causality. We also give a briefer account of the alternative framework of Franco and Eckstein which is based on Lorentzian spectral triples. We compare the two theories on the simple example of the product geometry of the Minkowski plane by the finite noncommutative space with algebra $M_2({\mathbb C})$.</subfield>
